f a hermeneutical theory of practice.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aExegese. 4aHermeneutik. 4aKanon. 4aMythos und Vernunft. 4amethodische Hybridität. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh  aExegesis.  acanon.  ahermeneutics.  amethodological hybridity.  amyth and reason.1 aAllolio-Näcke, Lars, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBecker, Uwe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeyer, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeyer, Andrea, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFischer, Irmtraud, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGertz, Jan Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHartenstein, Friedhelm, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIff, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoxter, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOorschot, Jürgen van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaur, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchellenberg, Annette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWagner, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWaschke, Ernst-Joachim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWitte, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1z97831113321920 cEPUBz97831113178470 cprintz978311131739740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311131756440uhttps://www.degruyter.